NodeBox is a node-based app on top of Processing for visual coders.

NodeBox uses OSGI to create bundles of nodes that can be versioned, updated and restarted safely.

To compile NodeBox:

  ant

To start NodeBox:

  java -jar lib/equinox.jar -console

Then at the prompt, type:

osgi> install dist/nodebox-core.jar
osgi> install dist/nodebox-builtins.jar
osgi> install dist/nodebox-app.jar
osgi> start nodebox.core nodebox.builtins nodebox.app

To quit:

osgi> exit

To see all running components, type:

osgi> ss

id      State       Bundle
0       ACTIVE      org.eclipse.osgi_3.6.0.v20100517
1       ACTIVE      nodebox.core_1.0.0
2       ACTIVE      nodebox.builtins_1.0.0
3       ACTIVE      nodebox.app_1.0.0